## Step 3: Deploy Frontend to Vercel

### 3.1 Create Vercel Account
Go to [https://vercel.com](https://vercel.com) and sign up/login.

### 3.2 Import Project
1. Click **"Add New..."** → **"Project"**
2. Import from GitHub: `Osinachi-cloud/sms_frontend`
3. Framework preset: **Next.js** (auto-detected)

### 3.3 Configure Environment Variables
In Vercel project settings → **Environment Variables**, add:

| Variable | Value | Environment |
|----------|-------|-------------|
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL` | `https://your-railway-url.up.railway.app/api` | Production |
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL` | `https://your-railway-url.up.railway.app/api` | Preview |

### 3.4 Update `vercel.json` (One-time)
In your `sms_frontend/vercel.json`, replace the placeholder backend URL:

```json
{
  "buildCommand": "next build",
  "outputDirectory": ".next",
  "framework": "nextjs",
  "installCommand": "npm ci",
  "rewrites": [
    {
      "source": "/api/:path*",
      "destination": "https://your-railway-url.up.railway.app/api/:path*"
    }
  ]
}
```

Commit and push this change:
```bash
git add vercel.json
git commit -m "chore: update backend URL in vercel.json"
git push
```

### 3.5 Deploy
Vercel auto-deploys on every push to `main`. Your frontend URL will be:
```
https://school-saas-frontend.vercel.app
```

